# Biochem / mat-growth progress logging

When the user shares **biochem_gnn or mat-growth** training outcomes (console logs, `compare.json`, cohort F1, “how did the run go”), update **[docs/MAT_GROWTH.md](docs/MAT_GROWTH.md)** only if the **locked baseline** or canonical leg changed (promote / new WC leg numbers). For detailed experiment tables, append to **[docs/archive/MAT_GROWTH_SIM_TODO.md](docs/archive/MAT_GROWTH_SIM_TODO.md)** or **[docs/archive/BIOCHEM_GNN_BASELINES.md](docs/archive/BIOCHEM_GNN_BASELINES.md)** unless they ask not to.

Legacy GNODE / corrector chronicles: **[docs/archive/BIOCHEM_TRAINING_PROGRESS.md](docs/archive/BIOCHEM_TRAINING_PROGRESS.md)** — update only if the run is on a restored legacy path.

## Metrics to prefer

- **Use**: deploy clot F1 / clot score / relaxed precision, wall / off-wall hop metrics, `mu_log_mae` when applicable.
- **Do not** treat collapsing aux losses alone as deploy success.

## Edit style

- Surgical edits; do not wipe archive chronicles.
- Record env knobs that mattered.
- If the user only asks a quick question with no new run data, answer without editing docs.
